
[1]profaneness

   PROFA'NENESS, n. Irreverence of sacred things; particularly, the use of
   language which implies irreverence towards God; the taking of God's
   name in vain.

   Profaneness in men is vulgar and odious; in females, is shocking and
   detestable.
